    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-08T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-08T12:00:00-05:00" n="646"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">455.006/9–451: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Belgium</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-08T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 8, 1951—1 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>315. Re <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 301, para A–2, if <gloss
                        target="#t_QR1">QR</gloss>s on US goods contemplated, <gloss
                        target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> shld remind Belgians their <gloss
                        target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss> obligations. <gloss target="#t_QR1"
                        >QR</gloss>s must conform requirements <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>
                    Arts XII–2(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) and XIV–1(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>). Also
                    Art XII–4(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) requires that prior to (or, if
                    impracticable, immediately after) imposition new restrictions <gloss
                        target="#t_CP1">CP</gloss>’s must be consulted re balance payments
                    difficulties, alternative measures, possible effect such measures on other
                        <gloss target="#t_CP1">CP</gloss>’s. We think Belg wld be well advised
                    initiate consultations if <gloss target="#t_QR1">QR</gloss>s contemplated since
                    if they do not others may at Sixth Session.<note n="1" xml:id="d646fn1">For
                        documentation regarding the problem of quantitative restrictions within the
                        framework of the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade (<gloss
                            target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>) and the United States position relating
                        thereto, see <ref target="frus1950v01#pg_692">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1950, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 692</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
